11/04/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament appointed Maxim Minchev as director general of the Bulgarian news agency BTA on Thursday (10 April). 
His predecessor, Stoyan Cheshmedzhiev, was dismissed last month, after protests by journalists working for him.
In other news, a 20-member delegation from the US NGO, the Council of Foreign Relations, began a two-day visit to Bulgaria on Friday. 
They will meet with cabinet members about NATO integration efforts and investment opportunities in the country. 
(Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa, Sega - 11/04/03; BTA - 10/04/03)
